This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for drug name recognition, which are typically covered under the arXiv sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of recurrent neural architectures for this task also suggests a focus on deep learning, which is a popular research area in both cs.CL and cs.LG.
